						<div class="postbody">Awesome - finally some conclusive results! Thanks for taking the time to do all these tests!<br /><br />Test 3 failing in this case is fine, since it was just me assuming the FDS' behavior.<br />Apparently writing $02 to $4022 will trigger an IRQ immediately if the reload value is $00 - so I guess the IRQ triggers whenever the timer is at 0, rather than when it reaches 0.  One thing left to test might be checking if turning on the irq repeat flag when the reload is 0 makes the irq fire in an infinite loop (I'm assuming it would)<br /><br />@Zepper I could be wrong, but I'm under the impression the FDSStick(?) is probably emulation the disk drive and its IRQs? (i.e the disk irqs probably can't be properly validated without actually writing the test rom to a FDS disk and loading that?)<br />I only have a vague understanding of how the disk loading &amp; its irqs work, to be honest, so I probably couldn't write a test for it even if I wanted to.</div>

